Contract Interaction Guide (Without UI)

This project can be fully tested using Remix IDE + MetaMask without requiring any frontend setup.

Prerequisites
Install MetaMask browser extension
Switch network to Sepolia Testnet
Ensure you have Sepolia ETH (use faucet if needed)
Open Remix IDE: https://remix.ethereum.org
Load Deployed Contracts in Remix
Go to "At Address" in Remix
Load contracts using deployed addresses:
TokenA: 0xa5A5CA63D5ce427A3E69F6FAB6cb379cc70039f9
TokenB: 0xB5FDE1d7f23E9315a0829AbDcC1E80bf15A1C2Ee
SimpleDEX: 0xb3bAA91E868CfC98492d547b5a4C173775d03E74
Use correct ABI (from your contracts)
Step-by-Step Interaction Scripts
1. Connect Wallet
In Remix → Deploy & Run
Select Injected Provider - MetaMask
Approve connection
2. Approve Tokens

Before adding liquidity or swapping:

Call on TokenA:

approve(DEX_ADDRESS, 1000000000000000000)

Call on TokenB:

approve(DEX_ADDRESS, 1000000000000000000)

DEX_ADDRESS = 0xb3bAA91E868CfC98492d547b5a4C173775d03E74

3. Add Liquidity

Call on SimpleDEX:

addLiquidity(
  1000000000000000000,
  1000000000000000000
)

Result:

Tokens transferred to pool
LP tokens minted
4. Check LP Token Balance

Call:

balanceOf(YOUR_ADDRESS)

(on LP Token contract if separate, or DEX if implemented internally)

5. Remove Liquidity

Call:

removeLiquidity(1000000000000000000)

Result:

LP tokens burned
TokenA and TokenB returned
6. Swap TokenA → TokenB

Step 1: Approve TokenA again (if needed)

Step 2: Call:

swapAtoB(AMOUNT)

Example:

swapAtoB(100000000000000000)
7. Swap TokenB → TokenA

Step 1: Approve TokenB

Step 2: Call:

swapBtoA(AMOUNT)
8. View Pool Reserves

Call:

reserveA()
reserveB()
9. View Spot Price

If implemented:

getPrice()

Or manually calculate:

Price = reserveB / reserveA

10. Arbitrage Execution

Call:

executeArbitrage()
If profitable → transaction succeeds
If not → transaction reverts
Minimal Script (ethers.js)

If needed, here is a simple script to interact programmatically:

import { ethers } from "ethers";

const provider = new ethers.providers.Web3Provider(window.ethereum);
const signer = provider.getSigner();

const dexAddress = "0xb3bAA91E868CfC98492d547b5a4C173775d03E74";

const dexABI = [
  "function addLiquidity(uint256,uint256)",
  "function removeLiquidity(uint256)",
  "function swapAtoB(uint256)",
  "function swapBtoA(uint256)",
  "function reserveA() view returns(uint256)",
  "function reserveB() view returns(uint256)"
];

const dex = new ethers.Contract(dexAddress, dexABI, signer);

// Add liquidity
await dex.addLiquidity(
  ethers.utils.parseEther("1"),
  ethers.utils.parseEther("1")
);

// Swap
await dex.swapAtoB(ethers.utils.parseEther("0.1"));

// Get reserves
const rA = await dex.reserveA();
const rB = await dex.reserveB();

console.log("ReserveA:", rA.toString());
console.log("ReserveB:", rB.toString());


